.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-password_gen \- Generate secure XKCD-style passphrases or high-entropy random strings, with entropy estimates and optional clipboard copying.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility password_gen
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate secure XKCD-style passphrases or high-entropy random strings, with entropy estimates and optional clipboard copying.
.SH FEATURES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBPassphrase mode\fP — combines random words from a built-in wordlist with a configurable separator
.IP \(bu 4
\fBString mode\fP — generates random character strings from a mixed alphanumeric and symbol charset
.IP \(bu 4
\fBEntropy display\fP — shows estimated bits of entropy for every generated result
.IP \(bu 4
\fBClipboard support\fP — copies output to clipboard using \fCwl-copy\fP, \fCxclip\fP, \fCpbcopy\fP, or \fCtermux-clipboard-set\fP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBInteractive mode\fP — running without arguments launches a guided prompt
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
bash _password_gen/_password_gen.sh

bash _password_gen/_password_gen.sh --mode passphrase

bash _password_gen/_password_gen.sh --mode passphrase --words 6 --separator _

bash _password_gen/_password_gen.sh --mode string --length 32

bash _password_gen/_password_gen.sh --mode passphrase --copy

bash _password_gen/_password_gen.sh --mode string --length 24 --copy
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Option   |   Description
\fC--mode passphrase\  |  string\fP   |   Generator mode (default: \fCpassphrase\fP)
\fC--words N\fP   |   Number of words in passphrase (default: \fC4\fP)
\fC--length N\fP   |   Character length for string mode (default: \fC20\fP)
\fC--separator CHAR\fP   |   Word separator for passphrase mode (default: \fC-\fP)
\fC--copy\fP   |   Copy generated output to clipboard
\fC-h, --help\fP   |   Show usage
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OUTPUT
.PP
.EX
  ------------------------------------------------
  Generated

  amber-beacon-velvet-prism

  ------------------------------------------------
  Entropy :  ~20.84 bits
  Mode    :  passphrase
  Words   :  4  (separator: -)
  ------------------------------------------------
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH ENTROPY REFERENCE
.PP
Mode   |   Settings   |   Entropy
Passphrase   |   4 words   |   ~20.84 bits
Passphrase   |   5 words   |   ~26.05 bits
Passphrase   |   6 words   |   ~31.26 bits
String   |   20 chars   |   ~123 bits
String   |   32 chars   |   ~197 bits
.PP
Entropy is calculated from the built-in 37-word list for passphrases and from a 72-character charset for strings. The bundled passphrase list is intentionally small and convenient; use string mode or a larger external wordlist for high-security secrets.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH CLIPBOARD SUPPORT
.PP
The tool tries these clipboard commands in order and uses the first one found:
.PP
Command   |   Environment
\fCwl-copy\fP   |   Wayland
\fCxclip\fP   |   X11
\fCpbcopy\fP   |   macOS
\fCtermux-clipboard-set\fP   |   Termux / Android
\fCclip.exe\fP   |   WSL / Windows
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP   |   Success
\fC1\fP   |   Unknown option or unsupported mode
